Sentencas: Seven compositions of (La1-xSrx)(0.99)FeO3-delta (x = 0, 0.05, 0.15, 0.25, 0.35, 0.50, 0.70) perovskites were synthesized using the glycine-nitrate method.
Titulo: Evaluation of LSF based SOFC cathodes using cone-shaped electrodes and EIS

Sentencas: The (La1-xSrx)(0.99)FeO3-delta compounds were characterized with powder X-ray diffraction, dilatometry, total conductivity and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy on coneshaped electrodes using a Ce1.9Gd0.1O1.95 electrolyte.
Titulo: Evaluation of LSF based SOFC cathodes using cone-shaped electrodes and EIS

Sentencas: Dilatometry shows that the thermal expansion coefficient of the (La1-xSrx)(0.99)FeO3-delta compounds increases with increasing strontium content.
Titulo: Evaluation of LSF based SOFC cathodes using cone-shaped electrodes and EIS

Sentencas: Total conductivity finds is maximum for LSF35.
Titulo: Evaluation of LSF based SOFC cathodes using cone-shaped electrodes and EIS

Sentencas: The activity of the (La1-xSrx)(0.99)FeO3-delta based perovskites towards the electrochemical reduction of oxygen was strongly dependent of the strontium content, the activity being highest for the composition (La1-xSrx)(0.99)FeO3-delta.
Titulo: Evaluation of LSF based SOFC cathodes using cone-shaped electrodes and EIS

Sentencas: The results indicates that Fe(III) is the catalytic active specie towards the electrochemical reduction of oxygen in a solid oxide fuel cell on (La1-xSrx)(0.99)FeO3-delta compounds.
Titulo: Evaluation of LSF based SOFC cathodes using cone-shaped electrodes and EIS

Sentencas: The results also show that oxide ion vacancies in the perovskite structure are important for the electrochemical reduction of oxygen.
Titulo: Evaluation of LSF based SOFC cathodes using cone-shaped electrodes and EIS

Sentencas: However, a negative effect of defect ordering (Sr2+ and oxide ion vacancies) is strongly indicated for the strontium rich compounds.
Titulo: Evaluation of LSF based SOFC cathodes using cone-shaped electrodes and EIS

Sentencas: Segregation of SrO to the surface might also play a detrimental effect on the activity towards the oxygen reduction reaction.
Titulo: Evaluation of LSF based SOFC cathodes using cone-shaped electrodes and EIS
